hopobject.body: Another year depo testosterone 100mg side effects Recently, Walmart announced that it was prepared to invest in Washington, D.C. and open six new stores, projected to create 1,800 jobs, albeit many at a mandated minimum wage rate of $8.25. But, the D.C. City Council voted to force them to offer a higher minimum wage of $12.50. Without a veto by the mayor, Walmart has since announced that they will pull out of the D.C. market, rather than pass along the higher labor costs to its customers.
